x4freetext: The target consisted of a thin carbon foil of
52+-2 mug/cm**2 thickness, with a LiF layer of
(960+-38)+E+15 at/cm**2 that was evaporated onto the
carbon foil and additionally with a thin gold layer of
4.4+-0.3 mug/cm**2 that was evaporated onto the LiF
layer for protection against wear and humidity
For the validation of the obtained differential cross
using thick, commercial and mirror-polished BaF(2) and
LiF targets. For beam normalization purposes Au was
evaporated onto the LiF thick target
The detection system consisted of four Si
surface barrier detectors, thickness of 1000 mum,
a HPGe detector of 80% relative efficiency
